            "title": "Global perspectives on religious tourism and pilgrimage",
            "abstract": [
                "\"This book adds to the knowledge in the field of religious tourism by providing readers with information on the international perspectives as well as the most current religious tourism practices used in both developed and developing countries. It also raises the level of awareness on the main studies carried out in the field of religious tourism\"--",
                "Section 1. Religious tourism and pilgrimage. Chapter 1. Discussing tourism as a rite of passage: a new fresh paradigm in tourism research ; Chapter 2. Authenticity and Buddhist experience: a multidimensional approach ; Chapter 3. Pilgrimage, tradition, and authenticity: the revival of the Chartres Pilgrimage ; Chapter 4. Mythical geographies: discussing the metaphor of lost paradise -- Section 2. Global perspectives on religious tourism and pilgrimage. Chapter 5. \"Beyond\" religious tourism: the case of Fez ; Chapter 6. Catholic pilgrimage in Europe: contemporary traditions and challenges ; Chapter 7. Religious tourism in South Africa: challenges, prospects, and opportunities ; Chapter 8. The lost paradise: the religious nature of tourism ; Chapter 9. Images of halal: a traveler's perspective on the halal market in Germany and Singapore ; Chapter 10. The economics of religious tourism Hajj and Umrah in Saudi Arabia ; Chapter 11. Dietary matters to which tourists with religious sensitivity pay attention during their vacation"
